item.title: Offically proven UFO's and Alien's Exist
item.dc:creator: @exps35 exps35
item.description:
@exps35 wrote:

[quote=“Moparisthebest, post:39, topic:382133”][quote author=exps35 link=topic=477935.msg3498616#msg3498616 date=1297549685]
The thing you guys don’t seem to consider is that – if there are any other sentient beings – odds are they are WAY further along than us (the human race is EXTREMELY young compared to the age of the universe).
and if you follow a philosophical belief: the more advanced they are, the more peaceful they are; if they are an aggressive race and they knew of our existence, they probably would have killed us by now.

What to do if you are the first human to make alien contact
[/quote]

That’s an interesting poster, but what it says and what you said aren’t true. Well, they could be, but they don’t have to be.

For example, why does a civilization have to be technologically advanced or be around thousands of years for interstellar space travel? What’s to say that they won’t have even developed the power of speech but still are able to travel to and around our planet just because they somehow don’t experience space and distance the way we do? Maybe they exist in some alternate dimension where 1ft = 100,000,000,000,000 light years in our dimension, and they can pop in between the different dimensions when ever they want?

Also, what’s to say 'alien’s aren’t already here? We have been on this planet for a long time, and have no idea what exists at the bottom of the oceans or more than a few miles under the surface of the earth. Why then, would it not be possible that intelligent life that has been around as long as us exists at depths of the oceans we can’t get to, or miles under the surface of the planet?

Basically the possibilities are endless, and we can speculate as much as we want, but the fact is we have no idea whatsoever.[/quote]

Eh, I would say probabilities point to the aforementioned, but that is merely my opinion.
I prefer to not think about dimensional theories, as it would be a complete mind-fuck, but I do agree that it is quite possible. Other factors that we take for granted could also very well not even exist in this ‘alien race’, such as their shape, size, body parts, etc. We judge if something exists or not from our sensory perceptions of that object, but what if they do not exist in the realms that we perceive? i.e. metaphysical beings

/lsd rant
